to the editor re merged hospitals gain both power and critics business day sept 26 hospitals may be enjoying new power but these mergers mean increasingly costly health care now hospitals can demand terms and since this concerns most hospitals in a given area health care plans must comply the plans must then raise costs leaving the public with higher rates another problem is the uncertainty of whether hospitals will drop plans that fail to meet their terms disruptions in treatment will occur as people lose their doctors or have to change plans the public can not shop around but must choose from plans the hospitals allow as merging hospitals keep gaining power over health care the public continues to wait for nonexistent benefits jennifer smith pittsburgh sept 30 2002

